article.description: Cal State Northridge 90, Long Beach State 83
article.headline: Cal State Northridge 90, Long Beach State 83
article.linkText: Cal State Northridge 90, Long Beach State 83
article.story: LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Jonathan Heard matched a season high with 24 points and Calvin Chitwood made three free throws in the closing seconds as Cal State Northridge beat Long Beach State 90-83 Saturday. It was the third straight win for the Matadors (9-7, 3-2 Big West Conference), who snapped a nine-game Long Beach State winning streak. Long Beach State (11-5, 2-1) trailed 86-71 with 2:14 remaining before Kejuan Johnson scored 10 of the 49ers' team's final 12 points, including eight in a 10-0 run to pull within five points with 30.8 seconds to play. But Chitwood, the conference leader in free-throw percentage, made three of four from the foul line in the final 14.2 seconds to seal the win. Johnson finished with 23 points and Sterling Byrd added 18 for the 49ers. Terrell Jones came off the bench to score 14 points for Northridge (9-7, 3-2), and Rai Colston came in to score 11.
